{"title":"Social care common inspection framework (SCCIF): residential holiday schemes for disabled children","public_updated_at":"2017-04-28T10:13:35Z","details":{"body":[{"content_type":"text/govspeak","content":"The SCCIF is for use from April 2017. \r\n\r\nOur first principle of inspection is to focus on the things that matter most to children’s lives. The SCCIF is not a ‘one-size-fits-all’ framework. The evaluation criteria are broadly consistent across the different types of children’s social care services but they reflect the unique nature of each type of service.\r\n\r\nA pdf version of this guidance is available on request. Please contact us at <socialcare@ofsted.gov.uk>.\r\n"},{"content_type":"text/html","content":"<p>The SCCIF is for use from April 2017. </p>\n\n<p>Our first principle of inspection is to focus on the things that matter most to children’s lives. The SCCIF is not a ‘one-size-fits-all’ framework. The evaluation criteria are broadly consistent across the different types of children’s social care services but they reflect the unique nature of each type of service.</p>\n\n<p>A pdf version of this guidance is available on request. Please contact us at <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#111;&#099;&#105;&#097;&#108;&#099;&#097;&#114;&#101;&#064;&#111;&#102;&#115;&#116;&#101;&#100;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#115;&#111;&#099;&#105;&#097;&#108;&#099;&#097;&#114;&#101;&#064;&#111;&#102;&#115;&#116;&#101;&#100;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a>.</p>\n"}],"child_section_groups":[{"title":"Contents","child_sections":[{"title":"1. Introduction ","description":"What the social care common inspection framework means.","base_path":"/guidance/social-care-common-inspection-framework-sccif-residential-holiday-schemes-for-disabled-children/1-introduction"},{"title":"2. The inspection principles ","description":"Focusing on children, being consistent, and prioritising resources. ","base_path":"/guidance/social-ca